	scalar shaders which speeds up rendering by a factor of 3.9 on average
	on SSE. The results are highly optimized, parallel shaders that operate
	directly on the internal data structures of a renderer. We show that
	both traditional shading languages such as RenderMan, but also C/C++-based
	shading languages, can be fully supported and deliver high performance
	across different CPU renderers.},
